        {
          "type": "heading",
          "attrs": {
            "level": 2
          },
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Method",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "heading",
          "attrs": {
            "level": 3
          },
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Roast the squash",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "orderedList",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "listItem",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Heat the oven to 200°C conventional. Spread the squash chunks across a large roasting tin in a single layer. Toss with a glug of oil and a generous pinch of salt. ",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "Roast",
                      "type": "text",
                      "marks": [
                        {
                          "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                          "attrs": {
                            "termId": "cmpry018s000060v4t58rt5af"
                          }
                        }
                      ]
                    },
                    {
                      "text": " for 30 to 35 minutes, turning once halfway, until golden at the edges and completely tender.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "heading",
          "attrs": {
            "level": 3
          },
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Build the soup base",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "orderedList",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "listItem",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "While the squash roasts, melt {{unsalted-butter}} of butter in a large saucepan over a medium-low heat. Add the {{onion}} onion and a pinch of salt. Cook for 8 minutes until soft.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "listItem",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Add the {{garlic}} of garlic, {{ginger-root}} of ginger, and {{cumin-ground}} of ground cumin. Cook for 1 minute, stirring.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "heading",
          "attrs": {
            "level": 3
          },
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Blend and finish",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "orderedList",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "listItem",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Add the roasted squash to the pan. Pour over {{stock-vegetable}} of hot vegetable stock. Simmer for 5 minutes.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "listItem",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Blend until completely smooth with a stick blender. Stir in {{double-cream}} of cream. Taste and season well.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "listItem",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Ladle into bowls and add a thin swirl of cream. Toasted pumpkin seeds are a good finishing touch.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "troubleshooter",
          "attrs": {
            "items": [
              {
                "fix": "Spread the squash in a single layer with space between pieces. Use two tins if needed. Crowd the tin and you steam; space them out and you roast.",
                "cause": "The pieces were too close together and steamed instead of roasting.",
                "symptom": "Squash is watery after roasting"
              },
              {
                "fix": "Add a small squeeze of lemon juice and a little extra salt to balance. A pinch more cumin also helps cut through the sweetness.",
                "cause": "The squash was very ripe, or over-roasted.",
                "symptom": "Soup is too sweet"
              },
              {
                "fix": "Roast for another 5 to 10 minutes until completely soft, then blend. A high-powered blender gives a smoother result than a stick blender for very fibrous squash.",
                "cause": "The squash was not tender enough before blending.",
                "symptom": "Texture is stringy after blending"
              },
              {
                "fix": "Return the tray to the oven for another 10 minutes until the squash shows golden-brown patches on the cut surfaces.",
                "cause": "The squash was not roasted long enough to develop caramelisation.",
                "symptom": "Colour is pale orange rather than deep"
              }
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "heading",
          "attrs": {
            "level": 2
          },
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Where this dish lives",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Butternut squash reached British supermarkets in the 1980s and became a soup standard in the 1990s. It blends to a very smooth purée and its sweetness suits most palates. The same recipe works as a weeknight supper or a dinner-party starter, depending on how carefully the bowl is finished.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
